<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5375306>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — A, Eocypraea (s.s.) dollfusi (de Laubrière, 1881), Lutetian (middle Eocene) of Fontenay-en-Vexin (Eure) (MNHN- DHT R63541) (leg. Pons); B, Eovolva nigeriensis (Newton, 1922), Bartonian (middle Eocene) of Bende Ameki (Nigeria) (MNHN- DHT R63539) (leg. Brébion). Scale bar: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5375306/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5375310>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. — A-C, Pseudocypraea dolini n. sp., Bartonian (Marinesian, middle Eocene) of Le Quoniam (Val d’Oise), holotype (MNHN- DHT R63008) (leg. J.-M. Pacaud); D-F, Pseudocypraea eratoformis (Hoernes & Auinger, 1880) n. comb., Langhian (middle Miocene) of Lapugiu de Sus (Rumania), holotype (NHMW 1999Z0077/0027). Scale bar: A-C, 5 mm; D-F, 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5375310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5375314>
    dc:description "FIG. 6. — Geographic distribution of the genera Pseudocypraea Schilder, 1927 and the fossil occurences." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5375314/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

